# 🌱 First Spring Boot Application

This is my first Spring Boot application created using **Spring Tool Suite (STS)** and **Maven**. The project demonstrates the basic setup of a Spring Boot application and how to run it successfully.

## 📌 Technologies Used

- Java 21
- Spring Boot 3.x
- Maven
- Spring Tool Suite (STS)
- Eclipse IDE

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
first-spring-boot-example
│── src
│   ├── main
│   │   ├── java
│   │   │   └── com/tutorialspoint/first_spring_boot_example
│   │   │       └── FirstSpringBootTest.java
│   │   └── resources
│── pom.xml
└── README.md
```

---

## 🚀 Features

- Created a Maven-based Spring Boot project.
- Configured project dependencies using `pom.xml`.
- Implemented the `@SpringBootApplication` annotation.
- Executed the application using `SpringApplication.run()`.
- Verified successful application startup.

---

## 🛠️ Prerequisites

Before running this project, ensure you have:

- Java 21 or later
- Maven
- Spring Tool Suite (STS) or IntelliJ IDEA
- Git

---

## ⚙️ Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/first-spring-boot-example.git
```

Navigate to the project directory:

```bash
cd first-spring-boot-example
```

Build the project:

```bash
mvn clean install
```

Run the application:

```bash
mvn spring-boot:run
```

or

Run the `FirstSpringBootTest.java` class directly from STS/IntelliJ.

---

